{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Option A — Minimal footprint (fastest to ship)\n    \n      \n        \n          💬 Reply publishing\n          Add replyPublishedAt + replyGbpId to existing Review model. \"Publish\" button calls GBP API.\n        \n        \n          📝 GBP Posts\n          New GbpPost table with draft/scheduled/published status. Cron job publishes scheduled items.\n        \n        \n          🖼 Photos\n          Stateless API bridge only. Upload → GBP API. View live photos fetched on demand. No local storage.\n        \n        \n          ❓ Q&A\n          Stateless API bridge. Fetch questions live, submit answers via API. No local storage.\n        \n      \n      \n        Auto-publish: New PUBLISH_GBP_REPLY automation step type — plugs into existing automation engine.\n      \n    \n    \n      Pros: Ships fastest (~4–5 weeks). Minimal schema changes. Cons: Photos and Q&A have no history. UX is inconsistent — some data is live, some is local. Hard to add analytics later.","choice":"minimal","id":null,"timestamp":1779991354674}
